HEADWORD: Rondle
<hw>Ron"dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Rondel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A rondeau.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A round mass, plate, or disk; especially
<fld>(Metal.)</fld>, the crust or scale which forms upon the surface of
molten metal in the crucible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rondo</ent>⟦br⟧
